{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# XGBoost Demand Prediction Pipeline — Milan\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook implements the XGBoost baseline for hourly carsharing demand prediction\n",
    "in Milan. It covers the full pipeline from data ingestion through spatial integration,\n",
    "feature engineering, model training, evaluation, and interpretability analysis.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Spatial unit:** ACE (Aree di Censimento) zones from the ISTAT 2011 Census.\n",
    "**Features:** Temporal variables (hour, day of week, month) and autoregressive lags.\n",
    "**Evaluation:** Hold-out (last 7 days) and 5-fold time-series cross-validation."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Configuration and Imports"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 21,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import geopandas as gpd\n",
    "from shapely.geometry import Point\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import matplotlib.dates as mdates\n",
    "import matplotlib.patches as mpatches\n",
    "import matplotlib.gridspec as gridspec\n",
    "import contextily as ctx\n",
    "import mapclassify as mc\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import xgboost as xgb\n",
    "import shap\n",
    "from scipy.stats import gaussian_kde\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import mean_absolute_error, mean_squared_error, r2_score\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import TimeSeriesSplit\n",
    "from trip_cleaning import parse_date_local\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.rcParams.update({\n",
    "    'font.family': 'serif',\n",
    "    'font.serif': ['Times New Roman', 'DejaVu Serif'],\n",
    "    'font.size': 10,\n",
    "    'figure.dpi': 150,\n",
    "})\n",
    "\n",
    "DPI = 300\n",
    "FIGURES_DIR = '../figures'"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Data Loading\n",
    "\n",
    "Three data sources are loaded:\n",
    "- **Trip data**: cleaned Parquet file filtered to Milan only.\n",
    "- **Census indicators**: ISTAT 2011 socioeconomic variables at the ACE level (Lombardy).\n",
    "- **Shapefile**: geographic boundaries of census sections (Lombardy), later dissolved into ACE zones."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 22,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": []
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "milano_trips = pd.read_parquet(\n",
    "    '../results/trips_cleaned.parquet',\n",
    "    filters=[('city', '==', 'milano')]\n",
    ")\n",
    "print(f\"Milan trips (cleaned): {len(milano_trips):,}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "indicadores = pd.read_csv(\n",
    "    '../datasets/R03_indicatori_2011_areecensimento.csv',\n",
    "    sep=';', engine='python', encoding='iso-8859-1'\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "milano_distritos = gpd.read_file('../datasets/lombardia_shapefile/R03_11_WGS84.shp')\n",
    "print(f\"Census sections loaded: {len(milano_distritos)}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Data Preprocessing\n",
    "\n",
    "Timestamps are parsed to local wall-clock time (Milan). Temporal features are\n",
    "extracted and trip coordinates are converted into a GeoDataFrame for spatial joining."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": []
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "milano_trips[\"s_date\"] = milano_trips[\"s_date\"].apply(parse_date_local)\n",
    "milano_trips[\"e_date\"] = milano_trips[\"e_date\"].apply(parse_date_local)\n",
    "milano_trips = milano_trips.dropna(subset=[\"s_date\"])\n",
    "\n",
    "columns_to_keep = [\n",
    "    \"vin\", \"traveltime\", \"google_time\", \"google_distance\",\n",
    "    \"s_date\", \"s_coord\", \"s_fuel\", \"e_date\", \"e_coord\", \"e_fuel\",\n",
    "    \"dist_km\", \"dur_min\", \"lat\", \"lon\",\n",
    "]\n",
    "milano_trips = milano_trips[columns_to_keep].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "milano_trips[\"hour\"]        = milano_trips[\"s_date\"].dt.hour\n",
    "milano_trips[\"day_name\"]    = milano_trips[\"s_date\"].dt.day_name()\n",
    "milano_trips[\"day_of_week\"] = milano_trips[\"s_date\"].dt.dayofweek\n",
    "milano_trips[\"month\"]       = milano_trips[\"s_date\"].dt.month\n",
    "\n",
    "milano_trips[\"geometry\"] = milano_trips.apply(\n",
    "    lambda r: Point(r[\"lon\"], r[\"lat\"]), axis=1\n",
    ")\n",
    "gdf_trips = gpd.GeoDataFrame(milano_trips, geometry=\"geometry\", crs=\"EPSG:4326\")\n",
    "print(f\"Trips ready for spatial join: {len(gdf_trips):,}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Spatial Integration with Census Data\n",
    "\n",
    "The shapefile CRS is set to EPSG:32632 (UTM 32N, native ISTAT projection) and then\n",
    "reprojected to EPSG:4326 to match the trip coordinates. A spatial join assigns each\n",
    "trip to its containing census section, and the ISTAT indicators are merged."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "milano_distritos = milano_distritos.set_crs(epsg=32632)\n",
    "milano_distritos = milano_distritos.to_crs(epsg=4326)\n",
    "gdf_trips = gdf_trips.to_crs(epsg=4326)\n",
    "\n",
    "trips_final = gpd.sjoin(gdf_trips, milano_distritos, how=\"left\", predicate=\"within\")\n",
    "\n",
    "viajes_sin_match = trips_final[trips_final['index_right'].isna()]\n",
    "total_sin_match = len(viajes_sin_match)\n",
    "print(f\"Trips without ACE match: {total_sin_match:,} ({total_sin_match / len(trips_final) * 100:.2f}%)\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "indicadores.columns = indicadores.columns.str.strip()\n",
    "if 'PROCOM' in indicadores.columns:\n",
    "    indicadores = indicadores.rename(columns={'PROCOM': 'PRO_COM'})\n",
    "\n",
    "merge_cols = ['PRO_COM', 'ACE'] if set(['PRO_COM', 'ACE']).issubset(indicadores.columns) else ['ACE']\n",
    "df_entrenamiento = trips_final.merge(indicadores, on=merge_cols, how='inner')\n",
    "print(f\"Trips after census merge: {len(df_entrenamiento):,}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. ACE Socioeconomic Maps\n",
    "\n",
    "Choropleth maps of four ISTAT Census 2011 indicators, dissolved to ACE zone level.\n",
    "These maps are used in Chapter 3 (employment rate) and Appendix A (remaining three)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "milan_sez = gpd.read_file('../datasets/lombardia_shapefile/R03_11_WGS84.shp')\n",
    "milan_sez = milan_sez[milan_sez['PRO_COM'] == 15146].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "milan_ind = indicadores[indicadores['PRO_COM'] == 15146].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "ace = milan_sez[milan_sez['ACE'] != 0].dissolve(\n",
    "    by='ACE', aggfunc={'Shape_Area': 'sum'}\n",
    ").reset_index()\n",
    "\n",
    "ace = ace.merge(\n",
    "    milan_ind.groupby('ACE')[['P1', 'P48', 'P52', 'P61']].sum().reset_index(),\n",
    "    on='ACE', how='left'\n",
    ")\n",
    "ace['area_km2']     = ace['Shape_Area'] / 1e6\n",
    "ace['pop_density']  = ace['P1'] / ace['area_km2']\n",
    "ace['employed_pct'] = (ace['P61'] / ace['P1'] * 100).fillna(0)\n",
    "ace['student_pct']  = (ace['P48'] / ace['P1'] * 100).fillna(0)\n",
    "ace_wm = ace.to_crs(epsg=3857)\n",
    "\n",
    "panels = [\n",
    "    ('pop_density',  'Population Density (inhab./km²)', 'YlGnBu',  '{:.0f}'),\n",
    "    ('employed_pct', 'Employment Rate (% pop.)',              'YlOrRd',  '{:.0f}%'),\n",
    "    ('student_pct',  'Students (% pop.)',                     'Blues',   '{:.0f}%'),\n",
    "    ('P52',          'Outbound Commuters (absolute)',          'Oranges', '{:.0f}'),\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "for col, title, cmap, fmt in panels:\n",
    "    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(8, 8), facecolor='white')\n",
    "    fig.suptitle(\n",
    "        f'Milan — {title} by ACE Zone (ISTAT Census 2011)',\n",
    "        fontsize=14, fontweight='bold', y=1.02\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    classifier = mc.NaturalBreaks(ace_wm[col].dropna(), k=6)\n",
    "    bins = classifier.bins\n",
    "    bins_rounded = np.round(bins, -2) if col == 'pop_density' else np.round(bins, 0)\n",
    "    bins_rounded = np.unique(bins_rounded)\n",
    "\n",
    "    ace_wm.plot(\n",
    "        column=col, cmap=cmap, scheme='UserDefined',\n",
    "        classification_kwds={'bins': bins_rounded.tolist()},\n",
    "        edgecolor='#555555', linewidth=0.3, legend=True,\n",
    "        legend_kwds={\n",
    "            'fontsize': 9, 'loc': 'lower left',\n",
    "            'title': title.split('(')[-1].replace(')', ''),\n",
    "            'title_fontsize': 10, 'frameon': True,\n",
    "            'framealpha': 0.92, 'edgecolor': '#cccccc', 'fancybox': True,\n",
    "        },\n",
    "        ax=ax, alpha=0.8,\n",
    "        missing_kwds={'color': '#f0f0f0', 'label': 'No data'},\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    legend = ax.get_legend()\n",
    "    for text in legend.get_texts():\n",
    "        raw = text.get_text()\n",
    "        parts = raw.split(',')\n",
    "        if len(parts) == 2:\n",
    "            lo = float(parts[0].strip().strip('(').strip('['))\n",
    "            hi = float(parts[1].strip().strip(')').strip(']'))\n",
    "            if np.isinf(lo) or np.isinf(hi):\n",
    "                continue\n",
    "            lo_str = fmt.format(round(lo))\n",
    "            hi_str = fmt.format(round(hi))\n",
    "            text.set_text(f'{lo_str} – {hi_str}')\n",
    "\n",
    "    ctx.add_basemap(ax, source=ctx.providers.CartoDB.Positron, alpha=0.35, attribution_size=5)\n",
    "    ax.set_title(title, fontsize=12, fontweight='bold', pad=8)\n",
    "    ax.set_axis_off()\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    filename = f'{FIGURES_DIR}/milan_ace_{col}.png'\n",
    "    plt.savefig(filename, dpi=DPI, bbox_inches='tight', facecolor='white')\n",
    "    print(f'Saved: {filename}')\n",
    "    plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. ML Dataset Construction\n",
    "\n",
    "### 6.1 Temporal Aggregation\n",
    "\n",
    "Trip counts are aggregated to the (ACE, date, hour) level. Socioeconomic indicators\n",
    "are summed within each ACE zone for later use in interpretability analysis."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df_entrenamiento['date_only'] = pd.to_datetime(df_entrenamiento['s_date']).dt.date\n",
    "dataset_ml = df_entrenamiento.groupby(['ACE', 'date_only', 'hour']).agg({\n",
    "    'vin': 'count',\n",
    "    'P1': 'sum',\n",
    "    'P48': 'sum',\n",
    "    'P52': 'sum',\n",
    "    'E3': 'sum',\n",
    "    'Shape_Area': 'sum',\n",
    "    'day_of_week': 'first',\n",
    "    'month': 'first'\n",
    "}).reset_index()\n",
    "\n",
    "dataset_ml.rename(columns={\n",
    "    'ACE_x': 'ACE', 'vin': 'target_demanda',\n",
    "    'P1': 'population_resident', 'P48': 'student_count',\n",
    "    'P52': 'outbound_commuters', 'E3': 'employed_resident'\n",
    "}, inplace=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "dataset_ml['demand_density'] = dataset_ml['target_demanda'] / (dataset_ml['Shape_Area'] / 1e6)\n",
    "dataset_ml['pop_density'] = dataset_ml['population_resident'] / (dataset_ml['Shape_Area'] / 1e6)\n",
    "print(f\"Aggregated dataset: {dataset_ml.shape}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 6.2 Zero Expansion\n",
    "\n",
    "A Cartesian product of (ACE zone x date x hour) is constructed to make zero-demand\n",
    "time slots explicit. Census-level attributes are forward/backward filled within each\n",
    "ACE group since they are time-invariant."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "start_date = dataset_ml['date_only'].min()\n",
    "end_date = dataset_ml['date_only'].max()\n",
    "all_dates = pd.date_range(start_date, end_date).date\n",
    "all_hours = np.arange(24)\n",
    "all_sections = dataset_ml['ACE'].unique()\n",
    "\n",
    "index_grid = pd.MultiIndex.from_product(\n",
    "    [all_sections, all_dates, all_hours],\n",
    "    names=['ACE', 'date_only', 'hour']\n",
    ").to_frame(index=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "dataset_full = pd.merge(index_grid, dataset_ml, on=['ACE', 'date_only', 'hour'], how='left')\n",
    "dataset_full['target_demanda'] = dataset_full['target_demanda'].fillna(0)\n",
    "dataset_full['demand_density'] = dataset_full['demand_density'].fillna(0)\n",
    "\n",
    "census_cols = ['population_resident', 'student_count', 'outbound_commuters',\n",
    "               'employed_resident', 'Shape_Area', 'pop_density']\n",
    "for col in census_cols:\n",
    "    dataset_full[col] = dataset_full.groupby('ACE')[col].transform(lambda x: x.ffill().bfill())\n",
    "\n",
    "dataset_full['date_only'] = pd.to_datetime(dataset_full['date_only'])\n",
    "dataset_full['day_of_week'] = dataset_full['date_only'].dt.dayofweek\n",
    "dataset_full['month'] = dataset_full['date_only'].dt.month\n",
    "dataset_full['date_only'] = dataset_full['date_only'].dt.date\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Before expansion: {dataset_ml.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"After expansion:  {dataset_full.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Zero-demand rows: {(dataset_full['target_demanda'] == 0).mean() * 100:.1f}%\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 6.3 Autoregressive Lag Features\n",
    "\n",
    "Lag features are computed after zero expansion so that missing time slots are\n",
    "represented as explicit zeros rather than NaN values."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "dataset_full = dataset_full.sort_values(['ACE', 'date_only', 'hour'])\n",
    "\n",
    "dataset_full['lag_1h'] = dataset_full.groupby('ACE')['target_demanda'].shift(1)\n",
    "dataset_full['lag_24h'] = dataset_full.groupby('ACE')['target_demanda'].shift(24)\n",
    "dataset_full['rolling_mean_3h'] = (\n",
    "    dataset_full.groupby('ACE')['target_demanda']\n",
    "    .shift(1).rolling(3).mean()\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Lag features added. NaN rows (insufficient history): {dataset_full['lag_24h'].isna().sum():,}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 6.4 Saving the Dataset"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "dataset_full.to_parquet('../results/xgboost/dataset_xgboost_milan.parquet', index=False)\n",
    "print(f\"Saved dataset: {dataset_full.shape[0]:,} rows, {dataset_full.shape[1]} columns\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Mean Demand Choropleth by ACE Zone\n",
    "\n",
    "Static publication-quality map of average hourly carsharing pickup demand per ACE zone.\n",
    "Demand values are annotated on zones with mean hourly pickups above 1.50."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "dataset_ml = pd.read_parquet('../results/xgboost/dataset_xgboost_milan.parquet')\n",
    "\n",
    "milano_shp = gpd.read_file('../datasets/lombardia_shapefile/R03_11_WGS84.shp')\n",
    "milano_shp = milano_shp.set_crs(epsg=32632).to_crs(epsg=4326)\n",
    "milan_only = milano_shp[(milano_shp['PRO_COM'] == 15146) & (milano_shp['ACE'] != 0)].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "ace_demand = milan_only.dissolve(by='ACE').reset_index()\n",
    "avg_demand = dataset_ml[dataset_ml['ACE'] != 0].groupby('ACE')['target_demanda'].mean().reset_index()\n",
    "avg_demand.columns = ['ACE', 'mean_demand']\n",
    "ace_demand = ace_demand.merge(avg_demand, on='ACE', how='left').fillna(0)\n",
    "ace_demand_wm = ace_demand.to_crs(epsg=3857)\n",
    "\n",
    "bins = [0, 0.75, 1.50, 2.50, 4.00, 5.50, 8.00]\n",
    "bin_labels = ['< 0.75', '0.75 – 1.50', '1.50 – 2.50', '2.50 – 4.00', '4.00 – 5.50', '> 5.50']\n",
    "ace_demand_wm['demand_bin'] = pd.cut(\n",
    "    ace_demand_wm['mean_demand'], bins=bins, labels=bin_labels, include_lowest=True\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "palette = ['#f0f9e8', '#ccebc5', '#7bccc4', '#43a2ca', '#0868ac', '#084081']\n",
    "color_map = dict(zip(bin_labels, palette))\n",
    "ace_demand_wm['color'] = ace_demand_wm['demand_bin'].map(color_map)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(10, 10), facecolor='white')\n",
    "ace_demand_wm.plot(color=ace_demand_wm['color'], edgecolor='#444444', linewidth=0.4, ax=ax, alpha=0.85)\n",
    "ctx.add_basemap(ax, source=ctx.providers.CartoDB.Positron, alpha=0.35, attribution_size=5)\n",
    "\n",
    "show_bins = set(bin_labels[2:])\n",
    "for _, row in ace_demand_wm.iterrows():\n",
    "    if row['demand_bin'] in show_bins:\n",
    "        centroid = row.geometry.centroid\n",
    "        ax.annotate(\n",
    "            f\"{row['mean_demand']:.1f}\",\n",
    "            xy=(centroid.x, centroid.y), ha='center', va='center',\n",
    "            fontsize=8, fontweight='bold', fontfamily='sans-serif', color='#1a1a1a',\n",
    "            bbox=dict(boxstyle='round,pad=0.2', fc='white', alpha=0.75, lw=0),\n",
    "        )\n",
    "\n",
    "legend_patches = [mpatches.Patch(facecolor=c, edgecolor='#888', label=l) for l, c in zip(bin_labels, palette)]\n",
    "ax.legend(handles=legend_patches, title='Mean Hourly Pickups', title_fontsize=11,\n",
    "          fontsize=10, loc='lower left', frameon=True, framealpha=0.92,\n",
    "          edgecolor='#cccccc', fancybox=True, borderpad=0.8, labelspacing=0.6)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.set_title('Milan — Mean Hourly Carsharing Pickup Demand per ACE Zone\\n(May–July 2015)',\n",
    "             fontsize=13, fontweight='bold', pad=14)\n",
    "ax.set_axis_off()\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig(f'{FIGURES_DIR}/milan_ace_demand.png', dpi=DPI, bbox_inches='tight', facecolor='white')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. Tweedie Distribution Fit\n",
    "\n",
    "Visual justification for the Tweedie loss function (`reg:tweedie` with p=1.5).\n",
    "The demand distribution exhibits a large point mass at zero and a long right tail,\n",
    "consistent with a compound Poisson-Gamma model."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": "df = pd.read_parquet('../results/xgboost/dataset_xgboost_milan.parquet')\ny = df['target_demanda'].values\n\np_tw = 1.5\nmu   = y.mean()\nphi  = y.var() / (mu ** p_tw)\nlam   = mu**(2 - p_tw) / ((2 - p_tw) * phi)\nalpha = (2 - p_tw) / (p_tw - 1)\nbeta  = phi * (p_tw - 1) * mu**(p_tw - 1)\nobs_zero = (y == 0).mean()\ntw_zero  = np.exp(-lam)\n\nrng = np.random.default_rng(42)\nn_sim = 100_000\nN_counts = rng.poisson(lam, size=n_sim)\nY_sim = np.array([\n    rng.gamma(shape=alpha, scale=beta, size=n).sum() if n > 0 else 0.0\n    for n in N_counts\n])\n\nfig = plt.figure(figsize=(14, 5.5), facecolor='white')\ngs = gridspec.GridSpec(1, 2, width_ratios=[1, 1], wspace=0.30)\nmax_val = 15\n\nax1 = fig.add_subplot(gs[0])\ncounts = np.bincount(y.astype(int), minlength=max_val + 1)[:max_val + 1]\nfreqs  = counts / len(y)\nx_vals = np.arange(max_val + 1)\nbars = ax1.bar(x_vals, freqs, width=0.75, color='#2196F3', edgecolor='white',\n               linewidth=0.6, alpha=0.85, zorder=2)\nbars[0].set_color('#1565C0')\nbars[0].set_alpha(1.0)\nax1.annotate(f'{obs_zero:.1%}', xy=(0, freqs[0]), xytext=(2.5, freqs[0] * 0.92),\n             fontsize=10, fontweight='bold', color='#1565C0',\n             arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', color='#1565C0', lw=1.5),\n             bbox=dict(boxstyle='round,pad=0.3', fc='#E3F2FD', ec='#1565C0', alpha=0.9))\nax1.set_xlabel('Hourly pickups', fontsize=11)\nax1.set_ylabel('Relative frequency', fontsize=11)\nax1.set_title('(a) Observed Demand — Milan', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold', pad=10)\nax1.set_xlim(-0.8, max_val + 0.8)\nax1.set_xticks(range(0, max_val + 1, 2))\nax1.grid(axis='y', alpha=0.25, zorder=0)\nax1.spines['top'].set_visible(False)\nax1.spines['right'].set_visible(False)\n\nax2 = fig.add_subplot(gs[1])\nsim_zero = (Y_sim == 0).mean()\nax2.bar([0], [sim_zero], width=0.4, color='#E65100', edgecolor='white',\n        linewidth=0.6, alpha=0.9, zorder=3,\n        label=f'$P(Y=0) = e^{{-\\lambda}} = {tw_zero*100:.1f}\\%$')\nax2.annotate(f'{sim_zero:.1%}', xy=(0, sim_zero), xytext=(2.2, sim_zero * 0.92),\n             fontsize=10, fontweight='bold', color='#E65100',\n             arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='->', color='#E65100', lw=1.5),\n             bbox=dict(boxstyle='round,pad=0.3', fc='#FBE9E7', ec='#E65100', alpha=0.9))\nY_pos = Y_sim[Y_sim > 0]\nkde = gaussian_kde(Y_pos, bw_method=0.15)\nx_kde = np.linspace(0.01, max_val, 500)\nkde_scaled = kde(x_kde) * (1 - sim_zero)\nax2.fill_between(x_kde, kde_scaled, alpha=0.35, color='#FF7043', zorder=2)\nax2.plot(x_kde, kde_scaled, color='#E65100', lw=2, zorder=4, label='Gamma density (positive values)')\nax2.set_xlabel('Hourly pickups', fontsize=11)\nax2.set_ylabel('Density', fontsize=11)\nax2.set_title(f'(b) Fitted Tweedie Simulation ($p = {p_tw}$)', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold', pad=10)\nax2.set_xlim(-0.8, max_val + 0.8)\nax2.set_xticks(range(0, max_val + 1, 2))\nax2.legend(loc='upper right', fontsize=8.5, framealpha=0.9)\nax2.grid(axis='y', alpha=0.25, zorder=0)\nax2.spines['top'].set_visible(False)\nax2.spines['right'].set_visible(False)\n\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.savefig(f'{FIGURES_DIR}/tweedie_fit.png', dpi=DPI, bbox_inches='tight', facecolor='white')\nplt.show()"
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 9. Model Definition and Training\n",
    "\n",
    "### 9.1 Hold-Out Evaluation (Last 7 Days)\n",
    "\n",
    "An XGBRegressor with Tweedie loss (p=1.5) is trained on all data except the last\n",
    "7 days, which serve as the hold-out test set."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "model_xgb = xgb.XGBRegressor(\n",
    "    objective='reg:tweedie',\n",
    "    n_estimators=500,\n",
    "    learning_rate=0.05,\n",
    "    max_depth=6,\n",
    "    random_state=42,\n",
    "    enable_categorical=True\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "dataset_ml['ACE'] = dataset_ml['ACE'].astype(int).astype('category')\n",
    "\n",
    "features = ['ACE', 'hour', 'day_of_week', 'month', 'lag_1h', 'lag_24h', 'rolling_mean_3h']\n",
    "target = 'target_demanda'\n",
    "\n",
    "dataset_ml['date_only'] = pd.to_datetime(dataset_ml['date_only'])\n",
    "dataset_ml = dataset_ml.sort_values(['date_only', 'hour'])\n",
    "\n",
    "fecha_max = dataset_ml['date_only'].max()\n",
    "fecha_corte = fecha_max - pd.Timedelta(days=7)\n",
    "\n",
    "train = dataset_ml[dataset_ml['date_only'] <= fecha_corte]\n",
    "test = dataset_ml[dataset_ml['date_only'] > fecha_corte]\n",
    "\n",
    "X_train, y_train = train[features], train[target]\n",
    "X_test, y_test = test[features], test[target]\n",
    "\n",
    "model_xgb.fit(X_train, y_train)\n",
    "preds = model_xgb.predict(X_test)\n",
    "preds_final = np.maximum(0, np.round(preds))\n",
    "\n",
    "mae = mean_absolute_error(y_test, preds_final)\n",
    "rmse = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_test, preds_final))\n",
    "r2 = r2_score(y_test, preds_final)\n",
    "\n",
    "denominator = (np.abs(y_test.values) + np.abs(preds_final)) / 2\n",
    "mask = denominator > 0\n",
    "smape = np.mean(np.abs(y_test.values[mask] - preds_final[mask]) / denominator[mask]) * 100\n",
    "\n",
    "errors = np.abs(np.round(y_test.values) - np.round(preds_final))\n",
    "acc_at_0 = np.mean(errors == 0) * 100\n",
    "acc_at_1 = np.mean(errors <= 1) * 100\n",
    "acc_at_2 = np.mean(errors <= 2) * 100\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"MAE:   {mae:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"RMSE:  {rmse:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"R2:    {r2:.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"sMAPE: {smape:.2f}%\")\n",
    "print(f\"Accuracy@0: {acc_at_0:.2f}%\")\n",
    "print(f\"Accuracy@1: {acc_at_1:.2f}%\")\n",
    "print(f\"Accuracy@2: {acc_at_2:.2f}%\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 9.2 Five-Fold Time-Series Cross-Validation\n",
    "\n",
    "`TimeSeriesSplit` ensures that each fold respects temporal ordering: the model\n",
    "is always trained on past data and evaluated on future data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "tscv = TimeSeriesSplit(n_splits=5)\n",
    "dataset_ml = dataset_ml.sort_values(['date_only', 'hour'])\n",
    "X = dataset_ml[features]\n",
    "y = dataset_ml['target_demanda']\n",
    "\n",
    "results_cv = []\n",
    "for i, (train_idx, test_idx) in enumerate(tscv.split(X)):\n",
    "    X_tr, X_te = X.iloc[train_idx], X.iloc[test_idx]\n",
    "    y_tr, y_te = y.iloc[train_idx], y.iloc[test_idx]\n",
    "\n",
    "    model_xgb.fit(X_tr, y_tr)\n",
    "    preds_tr = np.maximum(0, np.round(model_xgb.predict(X_tr)))\n",
    "    preds_te = np.maximum(0, np.round(model_xgb.predict(X_te)))\n",
    "\n",
    "    r2_tr = r2_score(y_tr, preds_tr)\n",
    "    r2_te = r2_score(y_te, preds_te)\n",
    "    mae_f  = mean_absolute_error(y_te, preds_te)\n",
    "    rmse_f = np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_te, preds_te))\n",
    "    errors = np.abs(np.round(y_te.values) - np.round(preds_te))\n",
    "    acc0 = np.mean(errors == 0) * 100\n",
    "    acc1 = np.mean(errors <= 1) * 100\n",
    "\n",
    "    results_cv.append({\n",
    "        'MAE': mae_f, 'RMSE': rmse_f, 'R2_train': r2_tr,\n",
    "        'R2_test': r2_te, 'gap': r2_tr - r2_te, 'Acc@0': acc0, 'Acc@1': acc1\n",
    "    })\n",
    "    print(f\"  Fold {i+1}: R2 train={r2_tr:.4f}  R2 test={r2_te:.4f}  gap={r2_tr - r2_te:.4f}  MAE={mae_f:.4f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "df_cv = pd.DataFrame(results_cv)\n",
    "print(f\"\\nMean +/- std:\")\n",
    "print(f\"  R2 test:  {df_cv['R2_test'].mean():.4f} +/- {df_cv['R2_test'].std():.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  MAE:      {df_cv['MAE'].mean():.4f} +/- {df_cv['MAE'].std():.4f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"  RMSE:     {df_cv['RMSE'].mean():.4f} +/- {df_cv['RMSE'].std():.4f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "model_xgb.fit(X_train, y_train)"
   ]
  },
